hearing seminar info page hearing seminar hearing seminar mailing list about hearing seminar english usa this mailing list is for people interested in announcements about upcoming talks the hearing seminar covers almost all topics related to auditory perception this includes physiology psychology speech music and many applications of perception research the hearing seminar is also offered for credit as music 319 one hour of credit is available no grades for participating in seminars more hours are available for students interested in auditory projects on a subject of mutual interest to the studnet and the instructor lectures both public and private are determined each quarter based on the availability of distinguished visitors and student's interets for an archive of old messages on this mailing list please check http mambo ucsc edu psl ccrmas ccrmas html to see the collection of prior postings to the list visit the hearing seminar archives using hearing seminar to post a message to all the list members send email to hearing seminar ccrma stanford edu you can subscribe to the list or change your existing subscription in the sections below subscribing to hearing seminar subscribe to hearing seminar by filling out the following form you will be sent email requesting confirmation to prevent others from gratuitously subscribing you this is a hidden list which means that the list of members is available only to the list administrator your email address your name optional you may enter a privacy password below this provides only mild security but should prevent others from messing with your subscription do not use a valuable password as it will occasionally be emailed back to you in cleartext if you choose not to enter a password one will be automatically generated for you and it will be sent to you once you ve confirmed your subscription you can always request a mail back of your password when you edit your personal options pick a password reenter password to confirm whi